WEBVTT

00:00:04.537 --> 00:00:06.639
Do you finally remember who I am?

00:00:06.706 --> 00:00:07.507
Yes.

00:00:07.574 --> 00:00:09.776
Your son shoplifted

00:00:09.843 --> 00:00:11.444
from my store.

00:00:11.511 --> 00:00:13.046
We shouldn't let him manipulate us
any further.

00:00:13.113 --> 00:00:14.948
What is he demanding?

00:00:15.015 --> 00:00:17.751
The victim is Hideyuki Sakuma,
40 years old.

00:00:17.817 --> 00:00:19.419
The bullet extracted from the body

00:00:19.486 --> 00:00:22.989
was fired from the gun that belonged
to Keisuke's father.

00:00:23.056 --> 00:00:24.324
I did it.

00:00:24.391 --> 00:00:25.458
Where's the gun?

00:00:25.525 --> 00:00:26.559
On the day of the wake,

00:00:26.626 --> 00:00:30.430
after we dug up the time capsule,
I buried it back in there.

00:00:30.497 --> 00:00:31.431
Your jacket button?

00:00:31.498 --> 00:00:34.134
It's missing. It’s the jacket
I was wearing when I met Sakuma.

00:00:34.200 --> 00:00:35.769
The police came.

00:00:35.835 --> 00:00:37.404
I have something I'd like to ask you.

00:00:37.470 --> 00:00:39.272
Would you mind coming
to the police station?

00:00:39.339 --> 00:00:40.673
Makiko's alibi fell apart.

00:00:40.740 --> 00:00:42.842
I need a little more time.

00:00:42.909 --> 00:00:44.544
I want to re-examine

00:00:44.611 --> 00:00:46.846
the incident that happened 23 years ago.

00:00:48.248 --> 00:00:49.783
The person who killed Oshima…

00:00:49.849 --> 00:00:51.251
was me.

00:00:51.317 --> 00:00:53.353
I can't imagine how Junichi must have felt

00:00:53.420 --> 00:00:54.821
after shooting someone.

00:00:54.888 --> 00:00:55.789
How did you cope with it?

00:00:55.855 --> 00:00:58.058
I don't think I deserve to be happy.

00:00:58.124 --> 00:01:01.261
I was scared of people finding out
who I really was.

00:01:01.327 --> 00:01:03.396
Did Naoto really do it?

00:01:03.463 --> 00:01:05.331
I feel like Naoto is covering for Makiko.

00:01:06.533 --> 00:01:08.501
Why Maki?

00:01:09.469 --> 00:01:12.605
I'm supposed to protect you, Maki.

00:01:14.340 --> 00:01:16.443
Does Makiko have the gun?

00:01:22.215 --> 00:01:23.249
Did Makiko

00:01:25.752 --> 00:01:27.954
shoot Hideyuki Sakuma with the gun?

00:01:28.021 --> 00:01:30.623
No, I’m the one who did it!

00:01:30.690 --> 00:01:32.358
Then what did you mean

00:01:32.425 --> 00:01:36.029
when you just said
that you’re going to protect Maki?

00:01:38.264 --> 00:01:39.099
Tell me what happened.

00:01:39.165 --> 00:01:41.167
So I shot my brother…

00:01:41.234 --> 00:01:43.603
You’re covering for Makiko, aren’t you?

00:01:48.441 --> 00:01:51.111
It’s fine because this is
what I want to do.

00:01:53.546 --> 00:01:55.515
And Maki understands too.

00:01:55.582 --> 00:01:56.549
What do you mean?

00:01:57.784 --> 00:02:00.453
Naoto. Naoto.

00:02:01.020 --> 00:02:02.021
Naoto!

00:02:04.724 --> 00:02:07.927
There are things that you
and Keisuke don't know.

00:02:07.994 --> 00:02:12.699
There are some things
that only Maki and I know.

00:02:51.171 --> 00:02:52.071
What…

00:02:52.672 --> 00:02:53.940
Oh hey.

00:02:54.007 --> 00:02:55.175
What brings you here?

00:02:55.241 --> 00:02:57.277
I was at Ms. Makiko’s salon.

00:02:58.511 --> 00:03:00.146
-Oh, it was today?
-Yeah.

00:03:01.114 --> 00:03:02.582
Is Ms. Makiko all right?

00:03:04.017 --> 00:03:05.752
She's not at the salon today.

00:03:07.453 --> 00:03:10.056
IWAMOTO

00:03:18.398 --> 00:03:20.366
Stop rushing me.

00:03:20.433 --> 00:03:21.267
Right there.

00:03:21.334 --> 00:03:22.635
See, right there!

00:03:22.702 --> 00:03:23.770
Take over for me.

00:03:23.836 --> 00:03:26.206
I'm counting on you. Don't mess up.

00:03:27.440 --> 00:03:29.442
-Hello?
-Has Makiko reached out to you?

00:03:29.509 --> 00:03:31.511
Not really. What's the matter?

00:03:31.578 --> 00:03:33.646
-Makiko is gone.
-What?

00:03:34.581 --> 00:03:36.049
I can’t get in touch with her.

00:03:36.749 --> 00:03:38.351
Keisuke, do you have her house key?

00:03:53.499 --> 00:03:54.901
Naoto!

00:03:55.835 --> 00:03:57.303
Long time no see.

00:03:57.837 --> 00:03:58.871
It's been a while.

00:03:59.606 --> 00:04:01.007
You're going to a prefectural university?

00:04:01.507 --> 00:04:03.910
It makes sense. You were always studious.

00:04:03.977 --> 00:04:06.045
And what are you planning to do, Maki?

00:04:06.112 --> 00:04:08.581
I want to become a hairstylist.

00:04:08.648 --> 00:04:09.782
A hairstylist?

00:04:10.350 --> 00:04:13.820
I'm planning on attending
a beauty school next year.

00:04:15.655 --> 00:04:18.157
-I think it'll suit you.
-Right?

00:04:18.725 --> 00:04:23.630
But to get a recommendation letter,
I need to improve my math grades.

00:04:26.432 --> 00:04:29.869
I remember I used to help you
with your math homework.

00:04:30.436 --> 00:04:32.772
I forgot about that.

00:04:36.776 --> 00:04:38.945
If you’d like, I can help you.

00:04:39.012 --> 00:04:40.613
With math?

00:04:42.081 --> 00:04:43.783
Yeah, if you’d like.

00:04:45.652 --> 00:04:47.620
That would be a big help,

00:04:47.687 --> 00:04:50.189
but you have to study
for entrance exams too, right?

00:04:51.257 --> 00:04:53.092
How about studying for two hours,

00:04:53.159 --> 00:04:57.297
one day a week?
That wouldn't be a problem for me.

00:04:57.864 --> 00:04:59.098
Really?

00:04:59.165 --> 00:05:00.600
Awesome.

00:05:01.100 --> 00:05:03.536
Then can you help me with this part?

00:05:04.037 --> 00:05:05.605
I couldn't figure it out.

00:05:05.672 --> 00:05:07.874
-This part is difficult.
-Right?

00:05:07.940 --> 00:05:11.210
For this, place the minus sign
in parentheses…

00:05:12.178 --> 00:05:14.714
Oh I see. The minus sign…

00:05:14.781 --> 00:05:16.983
Then I go like this…

00:05:50.116 --> 00:05:51.484
I'll go check upstairs.

00:05:59.092 --> 00:06:00.860
I think Makiko shot Hideyuki Sakuma,

00:06:01.494 --> 00:06:03.930
and Naoto buried the gun.

00:06:07.133 --> 00:06:08.501
On the night of the wake,

00:06:09.836 --> 00:06:12.672
when the four of us dug up
the time capsule, the gun was not there.

00:06:12.739 --> 00:06:14.474
You're saying Naoto buried it after that?

00:06:14.540 --> 00:06:16.309
Yeah, that’s what Naoto told me.

00:06:17.110 --> 00:06:18.311
So I went to check.

00:06:20.179 --> 00:06:21.314
But there was no gun.

00:06:21.381 --> 00:06:22.582
What?

00:06:22.648 --> 00:06:24.550
If anyone dug it up, it was Makiko.

00:06:29.589 --> 00:06:30.556
Junichi.

00:06:31.991 --> 00:06:33.626
There’s something I haven’t told you.

00:06:36.896 --> 00:06:37.930
Mr. Sakuma…

00:06:39.632 --> 00:06:40.533
I mean,

00:06:41.667 --> 00:06:42.802
that jerk

00:06:43.669 --> 00:06:46.906
wasn't satisfied with just the 300,000 yen
we initially gave him.

00:06:46.973 --> 00:06:49.342
Seriously? That's insane.

00:06:51.377 --> 00:06:53.513
He made further demands?

00:06:54.147 --> 00:06:55.047
Yes.

00:06:55.782 --> 00:06:57.583
What was his demand?

00:07:00.787 --> 00:07:04.390
That if we didn't do as he said, he'd
report it to Masaki's school the next day.

00:07:06.692 --> 00:07:08.594
What is he demanding?

00:07:11.164 --> 00:07:12.732
For Makiko to sleep with him.

00:07:14.033 --> 00:07:15.368
That's horrible!

00:07:19.005 --> 00:07:23.709
If you don't go see him alone tomorrow
at the same time, the deal is off.

00:07:24.610 --> 00:07:28.247
He says he’ll return the 300,000 yen,
and immediately contact the school.

00:07:29.749 --> 00:07:32.084
Let’s end this.
We should report this to the police.

00:07:32.151 --> 00:07:33.186
Wait.

00:07:33.252 --> 00:07:34.153
What?

00:07:34.821 --> 00:07:35.988
I'll think of a plan.

00:07:36.055 --> 00:07:37.657
Plan for what?

00:07:40.893 --> 00:07:42.228
Don’t tell me you’ll…

00:07:42.295 --> 00:07:44.764
No, I will never do that.

00:07:44.831 --> 00:07:46.365
Then what are you going to do?

00:07:52.171 --> 00:07:54.173
I’ll pay him more money.

00:07:55.508 --> 00:07:56.342
Money?

00:07:58.211 --> 00:08:00.813
This is a small town,
so I’ve heard the rumors about him.

00:08:00.880 --> 00:08:02.748
They say he's in debt from gambling.

00:08:03.583 --> 00:08:05.585
He must be desperate for money.

00:08:06.552 --> 00:08:09.956
If you pay money, you'll be paying him
for the rest of your life.

00:08:10.022 --> 00:08:12.325
I’ll try negotiating with him
one more time.

00:08:12.391 --> 00:08:15.228
No matter how you look at it,
there's no room for negotiation.

00:08:15.294 --> 00:08:17.230
Masaki's future is at stake.

00:08:18.531 --> 00:08:21.400
Just one more time.
If that doesn't work, I'll give up.

00:08:21.467 --> 00:08:23.302
I'll call the police right then and there.

00:08:27.607 --> 00:08:28.574
So,

00:08:30.009 --> 00:08:32.612
the two of you first met
at a restaurant at eight,

00:08:32.678 --> 00:08:34.280
then parted ways.

00:08:35.281 --> 00:08:37.483
You went to the hotel,

00:08:38.050 --> 00:08:40.920
and she lied
and said she went to the hair salon,

00:08:40.987 --> 00:08:43.356
but you don't know where she went.

00:08:43.422 --> 00:08:47.660
Then you met again at 10:30.

00:08:48.628 --> 00:08:49.462
Yes.

00:08:50.329 --> 00:08:54.133
Then we went to the store together
at 11:00 p.m.

00:08:54.200 --> 00:08:55.201
SMILE SAKUMA

00:08:55.268 --> 00:08:56.102
Okay, I’ll go now.

00:08:57.069 --> 00:08:59.071
I think I should go too.

00:08:59.138 --> 00:09:00.239
No, you should stay.

00:09:05.011 --> 00:09:05.845
Mr. Sakuma?

00:09:08.481 --> 00:09:09.515
I'm coming in.

00:09:41.247 --> 00:09:42.448
He’s dead.

00:09:43.950 --> 00:09:47.687
He was bleeding a lot from his stomach.

00:09:48.788 --> 00:09:51.190
What should we do?
Should we call the police?

00:09:51.257 --> 00:09:52.258
Let’s leave.

00:09:52.325 --> 00:09:53.626
Okay, yeah…

00:09:56.028 --> 00:09:57.063
What?

00:09:59.098 --> 00:10:00.633
Let’s get out of here.

00:10:00.700 --> 00:10:05.171
I said that we should
report it to the police!

00:10:06.572 --> 00:10:07.540
But

00:10:08.574 --> 00:10:10.543
it's also my fault
for not standing my ground.

00:10:10.610 --> 00:10:14.447
Did you see the gun, the murder weapon?

00:10:15.715 --> 00:10:16.582
No,

00:10:17.650 --> 00:10:18.851
I did not.

00:10:25.858 --> 00:10:26.959
This way.

00:10:27.660 --> 00:10:29.061
I have to get my things.

00:10:32.064 --> 00:10:34.800
The person you have called
cannot answer the phone right now.

00:10:35.301 --> 00:10:37.670
Please leave your name
and message after the beep.

00:10:42.708 --> 00:10:43.643
Makiko.

00:10:49.081 --> 00:10:50.516
Makiko is gone.

00:10:53.619 --> 00:10:56.355
Masaki's whereabouts are unknown as well.

00:11:06.966 --> 00:11:10.036
Makiko disappeared with Masaki,
and she has the gun with her.

00:11:13.439 --> 00:11:15.508
Do you understand what this means?

00:11:19.578 --> 00:11:23.582
There’s no way Makiko is fine with you
taking the blame for what she’s done.

00:11:28.220 --> 00:11:30.456
Junichi, you wouldn’t understand
how things are

00:11:30.523 --> 00:11:31.791
between Maki and me.

00:11:31.857 --> 00:11:33.225
Even if you take the blame,

00:11:34.927 --> 00:11:37.029
you can't save her from the fact
that she killed someone.

00:11:40.533 --> 00:11:42.401
I know that more than anyone.

00:11:49.709 --> 00:11:53.079
Plus, Makiko was driven into a corner
because you covered for her.

00:11:55.214 --> 00:11:56.482
She was driven into a corner?

00:11:56.549 --> 00:11:58.350
Makiko has the gun.

00:12:02.521 --> 00:12:04.390
There must be some bullets left.

00:12:06.592 --> 00:12:07.827
No way…

00:12:11.030 --> 00:12:13.566
Maki would never think of doing
anything like that…

00:12:13.632 --> 00:12:14.800
Naoto,

00:12:18.738 --> 00:12:19.672
I'm begging you.

00:12:23.109 --> 00:12:24.910
I want you to save Makiko.

00:12:31.717 --> 00:12:32.585
Please.

00:12:49.335 --> 00:12:50.436
I…

00:12:52.671 --> 00:12:54.006
lied.

00:12:56.142 --> 00:12:58.244
The truth is, I did not kill my brother.

00:12:59.678 --> 00:13:00.546
Oh, man…

00:13:08.287 --> 00:13:11.257
Why did you lie?

00:13:12.858 --> 00:13:14.527
Was it to cover

00:13:15.861 --> 00:13:17.463
for Makiko Iwamoto?

00:13:18.931 --> 00:13:22.201
Makiko Iwamoto killed Hideyuki Sakuma.

00:13:24.103 --> 00:13:25.271
Is that right?

00:13:27.373 --> 00:13:28.908
-I don’t know.
-But

00:13:30.910 --> 00:13:33.813
you thought Makiko Iwamoto did it.

00:13:36.015 --> 00:13:36.949
Why?

00:13:38.751 --> 00:13:39.718
That day,

00:13:40.953 --> 00:13:44.190
I returned from a business trip overseas.

00:13:48.294 --> 00:13:49.128
MAKIKO IWAMOTO

00:13:49.195 --> 00:13:52.064
I'm sorry,
I need to talk to you about something.

00:13:53.199 --> 00:13:56.302
Masaki shoplifted
at your older brother's supermarket.

00:13:56.368 --> 00:13:59.805
I was torn between going to Maki's house

00:13:59.872 --> 00:14:01.841
or going to where my brother was.

00:14:04.643 --> 00:14:06.545
In the end, I went to my brother's.

00:14:07.847 --> 00:14:11.350
When I got there,
the door to his office was open.

00:14:24.196 --> 00:14:25.431
And…

00:14:31.270 --> 00:14:34.874
Pachinko balls were strewn
all across the ground.

00:14:41.614 --> 00:14:42.982
Among the balls,

00:14:46.385 --> 00:14:48.120
I found a button identical

00:14:49.455 --> 00:14:51.357
to the ones on the jacket that Maki owns.

00:14:52.925 --> 00:14:54.560
I’m surprised you were able to tell

00:14:55.327 --> 00:14:57.229
that it was a button from her jacket.

00:14:57.830 --> 00:14:58.664
It was a jacket

00:14:59.932 --> 00:15:03.535
I had bought her as a souvenir
when I went on a trip abroad last year.

00:15:03.602 --> 00:15:05.571
A jacket for a souvenir, huh?

00:15:07.873 --> 00:15:09.608
Maki was taken aback by it too.

00:15:10.142 --> 00:15:12.344
Even more so,
because it was quite expensive.

00:15:14.613 --> 00:15:17.716
Maki, I'm sorry for not getting back
to your messages and calls.

00:15:18.417 --> 00:15:20.419
I forgot my smartphone
and went on a business trip.

00:15:22.955 --> 00:15:24.757
Sorry to bother you when you’re busy.

00:15:26.592 --> 00:15:27.760
No, I'm sorry too,

00:15:28.928 --> 00:15:30.296
about my brother

00:15:31.797 --> 00:15:33.332
causing you trouble.

00:15:35.267 --> 00:15:38.003
I'll talk to my brother.

00:15:40.472 --> 00:15:41.507
Thank you.

00:15:45.945 --> 00:15:47.813
Where are you right now? At home?

00:15:49.014 --> 00:15:52.584
No, I’m going to meet Keisuke
at a restaurant now.

00:15:54.620 --> 00:15:55.554
Okay.

00:15:57.122 --> 00:15:58.891
I'll talk to you tomorrow.

00:15:58.958 --> 00:16:00.192
Naoto.

00:16:01.360 --> 00:16:02.328
Yeah?

00:16:09.635 --> 00:16:10.703
It'll be all right.

00:16:16.542 --> 00:16:17.376
Okay.

00:16:22.114 --> 00:16:22.982
Bye.

00:16:31.256 --> 00:16:32.491
After that,

00:16:36.495 --> 00:16:40.299
I deleted the recorded footage
from my brother's phone

00:16:41.266 --> 00:16:42.735
and the store's security camera.

00:16:45.771 --> 00:16:47.006
And…

00:16:49.108 --> 00:16:50.843
What did you do with the gun?

00:17:01.520 --> 00:17:03.022
I didn't throw it in the river.

00:17:05.090 --> 00:17:06.658
Where's the gun?

00:17:11.230 --> 00:17:12.297
I…

00:17:16.035 --> 00:17:17.169
don’t want to say.

00:17:19.271 --> 00:17:21.273
Where's the gun?!

00:17:26.145 --> 00:17:29.281
Could it be that he hid that gun
in the same place

00:17:30.149 --> 00:17:34.153
where the four of you originally
hid that gun 23 years ago?

00:17:35.687 --> 00:17:37.890
A place only the four of you know about.

00:17:40.926 --> 00:17:41.760
Yes.

00:17:42.961 --> 00:17:44.496
Where is the gun?

00:17:46.198 --> 00:17:47.032
Sorry.

00:17:48.700 --> 00:17:49.935
Tell me where the gun is!

00:17:50.002 --> 00:17:52.271
Where's the gun? Where's the damn gun?!

00:18:00.479 --> 00:18:04.450
At this time, there's no physical evidence
that proves Makiko Iwamoto is the culprit.

00:18:04.516 --> 00:18:06.485
However, based on circumstantial evidence,

00:18:06.552 --> 00:18:10.189
it seems highly likely
that she was involved in the crime.

00:18:10.255 --> 00:18:12.791
Furthermore, it appears
she has disappeared with her son.

00:18:14.426 --> 00:18:18.163
Is it possible
that she currently has the gun?

00:18:18.230 --> 00:18:19.598
Yes, it’s highly likely.

00:18:20.799 --> 00:18:23.102
Where did she get the gun?

00:18:23.168 --> 00:18:24.369
We don’t know yet.

00:18:27.339 --> 00:18:28.941
Shift the direction of our investigation.

00:18:29.007 --> 00:18:32.644
We will now focus all our efforts
on the investigation of Makiko Iwamoto.

00:18:32.711 --> 00:18:34.379
Effective immediately,

00:18:34.446 --> 00:18:37.616
Makiko Iwamoto is considered
a key person of interest in this case,

00:18:37.683 --> 00:18:40.586
and her apprehension
will be our top priority.

00:18:40.652 --> 00:18:42.254
Yes, sir.

00:18:44.456 --> 00:18:47.092
We're so high up!

00:18:50.662 --> 00:18:52.865
We're going up again!

00:18:55.200 --> 00:18:56.135
I'm scared!

00:19:02.374 --> 00:19:03.876
Look how high up it goes.

00:19:03.942 --> 00:19:05.544
See? It goes up so high.

00:19:05.611 --> 00:19:07.846
Let's see, what time was the dolphin show?

00:19:07.913 --> 00:19:09.414
I'm so tired.

00:19:09.481 --> 00:19:11.016
-What?
-I'm tired.

00:19:11.083 --> 00:19:12.551
No way.

00:19:12.618 --> 00:19:14.319
You can rest
while watching the dolphin show.

00:19:14.386 --> 00:19:15.988
I want to take a break.

00:19:16.054 --> 00:19:17.656
Come on, let's watch the show.

00:19:17.723 --> 00:19:20.325
Seriously? We did a lot already.

00:19:21.360 --> 00:19:23.095
I wanted to see the show.

00:19:23.162 --> 00:19:24.863
I don't want to. I'm tired.

00:19:29.568 --> 00:19:31.136
I got some nuggets.

00:19:31.703 --> 00:19:33.172
-I want the boba drink.
-Here.

00:19:33.238 --> 00:19:37.276
I want to eat the nuggets,
but I'm going to the bathroom first.

00:19:37.342 --> 00:19:38.343
-What?
-I'll be back.

00:19:38.410 --> 00:19:40.245
-You know where the bathroom is?
-Yup.

00:19:52.491 --> 00:19:54.526
JUNICHI

00:20:05.070 --> 00:20:06.038
Makiko.

00:20:08.173 --> 00:20:09.141
I want to see you.

00:20:12.444 --> 00:20:13.645
I want to see you right now.

00:20:44.276 --> 00:20:45.978
I have to tell you something, Masaki.

00:20:48.046 --> 00:20:48.981
What is it?

00:20:51.917 --> 00:20:52.918
I

00:20:55.287 --> 00:20:57.122
have to go to the police station,

00:20:59.625 --> 00:21:02.661
so I might not be able
to see you for a while.

00:21:04.630 --> 00:21:05.464
Why?

00:21:10.669 --> 00:21:13.372
I did something that will get me arrested,

00:21:15.474 --> 00:21:16.475
but I kept quiet about it.

00:21:20.312 --> 00:21:21.980
That's why I'm going to turn myself in.

00:21:27.119 --> 00:21:28.420
What did you do?

00:21:33.058 --> 00:21:36.995
I want to tell you,

00:21:38.163 --> 00:21:41.300
but I don’t know how.

00:21:44.670 --> 00:21:46.238
I didn't know what to do,

00:21:47.272 --> 00:21:49.675
and time just kept passing by…

00:21:56.415 --> 00:21:58.417
But I have to take responsibility now.

00:22:11.630 --> 00:22:13.265
What I know for sure is that…

00:22:18.470 --> 00:22:20.772
What I have done

00:22:21.373 --> 00:22:24.776
will end up hurting you.

00:22:32.784 --> 00:22:33.819
I’m sorry.

00:22:42.427 --> 00:22:43.962
I’m sorry, Masaki.

00:23:07.986 --> 00:23:09.621
We'll leave you here, Mr. Sakuma.

00:23:09.688 --> 00:23:10.522
Thank you.

00:23:11.223 --> 00:23:12.057
Take care.

00:23:15.961 --> 00:23:16.862
MITSUBA POLICE STATION

00:23:16.928 --> 00:23:19.731
Chief! What are you doing?

00:23:19.798 --> 00:23:20.966
What are these? Weeds?

00:23:21.032 --> 00:23:22.768
They're not weeds. They're pansies.

00:23:22.834 --> 00:23:24.035
Move. Move out of my way.

00:23:24.102 --> 00:23:25.937
Sorry. Wait, I'll help you out.

00:23:26.004 --> 00:23:27.873
Here, I can take this.

00:23:29.741 --> 00:23:31.009
-What are you doing?
-Sorry!

00:23:31.076 --> 00:23:32.944
-No need to help me.
-It's okay, I can do it.

00:23:33.011 --> 00:23:33.845
-Forget it.
-It's okay.

00:23:33.912 --> 00:23:34.579
IWAMOTO

00:23:34.646 --> 00:23:37.082
Why did that detective

00:23:37.916 --> 00:23:41.686
keep quiet about us hiding the gun?

00:23:42.621 --> 00:23:44.956
I think it's to solve the case
from 23 years ago.

00:23:46.124 --> 00:23:47.826
I don’t understand.

00:23:48.326 --> 00:23:50.195
I don’t know what she has planned either,

00:23:51.963 --> 00:23:54.199
but I’m sure she has something in mind.

00:23:55.434 --> 00:23:58.136
When did Makiko even get her hands
on that gun?

00:24:00.205 --> 00:24:02.507
I dug up the time capsule on Friday night.

00:24:13.752 --> 00:24:16.154
The gun was no longer there at that time.

00:24:17.823 --> 00:24:19.991
I don’t even know when she dug it up,

00:24:20.058 --> 00:24:22.561
and I can’t imagine she dug it up
to kill Sakuma either.

00:24:23.061 --> 00:24:25.864
I just can't believe
that Makiko dug it up.

00:24:31.536 --> 00:24:32.404
Naoto.

00:24:35.740 --> 00:24:37.442
No matter how we look at it,
it has to be you.

00:24:46.017 --> 00:24:47.085
Yeah,

00:24:50.222 --> 00:24:51.990
I dug it up.

00:24:53.692 --> 00:24:54.593
When?

00:24:57.529 --> 00:24:59.331
During my third year of high school.

00:24:59.898 --> 00:25:02.367
Third year of high school? Why?

00:25:06.705 --> 00:25:08.406
I wanted to kill my brother.

00:25:11.610 --> 00:25:14.479
-What the hell?
-I was serious.

00:25:16.982 --> 00:25:18.683
I seriously wanted to kill him,

00:25:19.484 --> 00:25:20.519
so I dug it up.

00:25:43.608 --> 00:25:45.076
I took the gun

00:25:46.278 --> 00:25:47.612
and went to my brother's room.

00:25:59.057 --> 00:26:00.425
You’re not going to shoot?

00:26:06.164 --> 00:26:07.532
Don’t move.

00:26:10.168 --> 00:26:12.237
Give me that gun.

00:26:16.074 --> 00:26:19.377
Wow, it’s made so well.

00:26:20.312 --> 00:26:22.414
Give it back.

00:26:26.785 --> 00:26:30.255
Stop. Stop it!

00:26:33.391 --> 00:26:34.659
Is this a real gun?

00:26:34.726 --> 00:26:36.227
Help!

00:26:37.195 --> 00:26:39.598
How did you even get this?

00:26:39.664 --> 00:26:41.933
This is hilarious!

00:26:42.000 --> 00:26:44.669
So Hideyuki Sakuma had that gun
ever since that day,

00:26:46.338 --> 00:26:48.907
and then Makiko went to Sakuma's place,
and something happened.

00:26:51.576 --> 00:26:53.478
I never imagined she'd go there
on her own.

00:26:59.150 --> 00:27:00.852
Why didn't I realize
that she might do that?

00:27:01.419 --> 00:27:02.954
Why do you think she went by herself?

00:27:04.389 --> 00:27:06.925
There's no way she went there
to give in to my brother's demands.

00:27:06.992 --> 00:27:10.528
I know she didn't do that either!

00:27:10.595 --> 00:27:11.463
Naoto.

00:27:13.598 --> 00:27:15.900
What made you want to kill your brother?

00:27:24.542 --> 00:27:26.444
As bad as your brother was,

00:27:26.511 --> 00:27:28.847
the fact that you wanted to kill him
with a gun,

00:27:31.182 --> 00:27:32.984
means something
truly horrible happened, right?

00:27:37.589 --> 00:27:38.990
Back then,

00:27:41.059 --> 00:27:43.061
if you two were around,

00:27:44.996 --> 00:27:47.799
I know you guys would've beaten
my older brother to a pulp.

00:27:50.301 --> 00:27:52.537
But you two had moved away.

00:27:54.406 --> 00:27:55.640
What happened?

00:28:01.913 --> 00:28:03.281
I can’t tell you.

00:28:05.684 --> 00:28:08.486
Because I have to protect Maki.

00:28:13.591 --> 00:28:14.726
Maki?

00:28:23.568 --> 00:28:24.402
MAKIKO

00:28:24.469 --> 00:28:25.603
It's from Makiko.

00:28:30.642 --> 00:28:31.843
Welcome back.

00:28:34.612 --> 00:28:35.547
Hiromi.

00:28:36.414 --> 00:28:38.783
I want you to go somewhere with me
right now.

00:28:38.850 --> 00:28:39.784
What?

00:28:41.086 --> 00:28:44.556
It's regarding Makiko,
but I need you to do me a favor.

00:28:48.093 --> 00:28:49.127
-Sorry.
-It's okay.

00:28:59.704 --> 00:29:01.506
-Masaki.
-Dad.

00:29:07.078 --> 00:29:09.047
I'll be here to protect you, Masaki.

00:29:11.783 --> 00:29:12.884
What about Mom?

00:29:16.421 --> 00:29:17.422
She'll be all right.

00:29:19.791 --> 00:29:20.625
We'll be with her.

00:29:22.327 --> 00:29:25.597
We'll always be with you and Makiko.

00:29:34.973 --> 00:29:35.907
It'll be all right.

00:29:37.041 --> 00:29:38.543
We're here to discuss the next step.

00:29:42.113 --> 00:29:45.016
Masaki, why don't we hang out
while we wait for them?

00:29:49.921 --> 00:29:50.989
Wait for me.

00:29:57.562 --> 00:29:58.930
Please look after him.

00:29:59.864 --> 00:30:01.666
Okay. Let's go.

00:30:03.334 --> 00:30:05.003
I heard about the aquarium.

00:30:05.770 --> 00:30:06.805
Let's check it out.

00:30:09.974 --> 00:30:11.242
I'm sorry.

00:30:11.810 --> 00:30:13.878
I haven't been able to tell the truth
until now.

00:30:15.647 --> 00:30:17.115
I'm the one who killed

00:30:18.483 --> 00:30:19.417
Sakuma.

00:30:25.423 --> 00:30:26.624
Where's the gun right now?

00:30:30.061 --> 00:30:31.062
It's in here.

00:30:32.864 --> 00:30:34.599
Why are you doing this, Maki?

00:30:35.633 --> 00:30:36.968
Sorry, Naoto.

00:30:38.136 --> 00:30:40.471
I know you were trying to protect
Masaki and me.

00:30:40.972 --> 00:30:42.674
I wish you would've let me.

00:30:44.375 --> 00:30:45.510
Thank you.

00:30:47.045 --> 00:30:47.879
But

00:30:49.747 --> 00:30:52.917
all of this happened because I tried
to hide the shoplifting incident.

00:30:56.120 --> 00:30:58.756
So I don't want to make
that same mistake again,

00:31:01.626 --> 00:31:05.597
and I can't pretend
that I didn't kill him either.

00:31:07.165 --> 00:31:08.566
Why did you go by yourself?

00:31:11.502 --> 00:31:13.071
I wanted to end it.

00:31:16.875 --> 00:31:18.009
I never

00:31:19.644 --> 00:31:22.981
wanted to let Sakuma get his way with me
ever again.

00:31:25.817 --> 00:31:26.784
What do you mean?

00:31:29.621 --> 00:31:31.789
Okay, then what's "hikigane"?

00:31:32.290 --> 00:31:33.992
-Trigger.
-Correct.

00:31:34.058 --> 00:31:35.059
Hooray.

00:31:35.126 --> 00:31:36.694
Sorry for staying so late.

00:31:37.729 --> 00:31:39.597
-See you again next week.
-Yeah.

00:31:39.664 --> 00:31:40.965
See you.

00:31:41.032 --> 00:31:43.368
-Bye.
-Bye.

00:31:57.115 --> 00:31:58.283
Hey.

00:32:05.023 --> 00:32:08.459
That impertinent woman
was here again, huh?

00:32:12.330 --> 00:32:14.565
I'll be able to sleep well tonight.

00:32:25.476 --> 00:32:27.812
Maki, you don't have to say it.

00:32:33.851 --> 00:32:36.721
-I--
-Don't say it! It'll only cause you pain.

00:33:12.123 --> 00:33:14.625
In the third year of high school,
I was raped by Sakuma.

00:33:20.631 --> 00:33:21.933
Maki.

00:33:26.504 --> 00:33:27.839
Maki.

00:33:53.531 --> 00:33:55.166
I'm okay.

00:33:55.233 --> 00:33:57.368
I fought back and he ran away.

00:33:57.435 --> 00:33:58.736
I'm okay.

00:34:03.875 --> 00:34:04.942
That day,

00:34:06.611 --> 00:34:08.713
when I got home, my parents looked at me,

00:34:09.480 --> 00:34:13.151
and they immediately realized
what had happened.

00:34:14.585 --> 00:34:18.122
And a week later we moved to Yokohama.

00:34:21.626 --> 00:34:25.029
My parents and I
tried to pretend it never happened.

00:34:28.633 --> 00:34:31.302
It was hard for me to just pretend
like it never happened,

00:34:32.770 --> 00:34:35.373
and I struggled for a long time.

00:34:38.109 --> 00:34:40.078
But I went to beauty school,

00:34:41.879 --> 00:34:44.182
and I realized that it was okay
for me to be happy.

00:34:45.083 --> 00:34:48.219
I decided that I was
going to become happy.

00:34:53.391 --> 00:34:55.092
It was around that time

00:34:55.993 --> 00:34:58.396
when I reunited with Keisuke.

00:34:58.896 --> 00:35:01.599
You're Ms. Makiko Iwamoto, right?

00:35:02.100 --> 00:35:02.934
What?

00:35:03.601 --> 00:35:04.702
Keisuke?

00:35:05.503 --> 00:35:06.370
Hey.

00:35:09.207 --> 00:35:13.277
After that, there were times when
I found myself laughing with all my heart.

00:35:13.878 --> 00:35:17.915
Before I knew it,
I was laughing more often than not.

00:35:19.750 --> 00:35:23.454
When we got married and he suggested
we live in Mitsuba,

00:35:24.021 --> 00:35:26.224
I was almost taken back in time again,

00:35:28.759 --> 00:35:30.394
but I didn't want

00:35:32.063 --> 00:35:34.532
to let that incident control my life.

00:35:34.599 --> 00:35:36.501
Thanks for waiting.

00:35:37.301 --> 00:35:38.703
What brings you guys here?

00:35:42.373 --> 00:35:44.542
-You guys are getting married?
-Yeah.

00:35:47.478 --> 00:35:48.312
This is for you.

00:35:49.747 --> 00:35:51.582
Please come to our wedding.

00:35:53.084 --> 00:35:54.085
Congratulations.

00:35:54.585 --> 00:35:56.320
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

00:35:57.188 --> 00:36:01.092
When you came to that house
to deliver the wedding invitation,

00:36:02.927 --> 00:36:04.762
I sensed your resolve, Maki.

00:36:07.865 --> 00:36:11.636
Then Masaki was born, and I was so happy.

00:36:14.438 --> 00:36:16.674
I'm so glad we got married.

00:36:20.411 --> 00:36:23.147
That day,
I went to Sakuma's place by myself

00:36:24.682 --> 00:36:25.883
because to me,

00:36:27.185 --> 00:36:29.387
that was the only option I had.

00:36:36.327 --> 00:36:40.198
You're here early.
We're supposed to meet at 11:00.

00:36:41.766 --> 00:36:42.833
Should I leave?

00:36:44.535 --> 00:36:45.770
You're alone?

00:36:48.573 --> 00:36:49.407
Yes.

00:36:50.341 --> 00:36:51.509
Come inside.

00:36:59.717 --> 00:37:03.821
I thought for sure that damn Kiyohara
would come along too.

00:37:06.757 --> 00:37:08.192
Now then…

00:37:09.493 --> 00:37:13.531
I'm fine doing it here,
but want to go to a hotel?

00:37:14.198 --> 00:37:15.233
What do you want to do?

00:37:20.104 --> 00:37:21.439
Give me the data.

00:37:23.541 --> 00:37:24.375
What?

00:37:25.543 --> 00:37:29.647
You were supposed to give it to us
yesterday in exchange for 300,000 yen.

00:37:29.714 --> 00:37:32.016
Stop with that boring stuff.

00:37:36.354 --> 00:37:37.822
Give me the data.

00:37:42.760 --> 00:37:43.961
Shall we

00:37:45.596 --> 00:37:47.565
do it outside after all?

00:37:49.100 --> 00:37:50.701
Like we did back then?

00:37:53.070 --> 00:37:54.572
Don't touch me!

00:37:58.009 --> 00:38:00.911
Fine. I'll give it to you.

00:38:07.985 --> 00:38:10.655
I have one million yen here.

00:38:11.889 --> 00:38:14.058
Take this and let's--

00:38:14.558 --> 00:38:16.794
Don't get cocky with me!

00:38:32.310 --> 00:38:34.178
Don't you feel like we're bound by fate?

00:38:35.680 --> 00:38:36.580
We

00:38:37.815 --> 00:38:40.251
can't escape this fate.

00:38:55.499 --> 00:38:57.868
You're as impertinent as ever.

00:38:59.403 --> 00:39:02.540
Don't you see that this is
our fateful reunion?

00:39:14.885 --> 00:39:18.489
But I find that impertinent attitude
irresistible.

00:40:06.337 --> 00:40:08.906
Maki, I'm sorry for not getting back
to your messages and calls.

00:40:09.707 --> 00:40:11.509
Sorry to bother you when you’re busy.

00:40:12.943 --> 00:40:15.446
No, I'm sorry too…

00:41:06.096 --> 00:41:07.665
Of course we're going.

00:41:09.967 --> 00:41:12.069
-I'll go too.
-Okay, let's go.

00:41:32.823 --> 00:41:36.861
I shot the manager
of Smile Sakuma with a gun.

00:41:46.170 --> 00:41:47.671
The gun is inside.

00:41:51.442 --> 00:41:53.010
The time is 7:04 p.m.

00:41:54.778 --> 00:41:57.281
We're placing you under arrest for murder.

00:42:28.612 --> 00:42:29.513
I knew

00:42:30.347 --> 00:42:32.550
you'd bring the gun to me.

00:42:35.386 --> 00:42:36.420
What do you mean?

00:42:37.354 --> 00:42:40.624
We'll finally find out the truth
about what happened 23 years ago.

00:42:41.926 --> 00:42:43.193
Detective Tobina,

00:42:45.095 --> 00:42:48.566
there's a chance you didn't kill Oshima.

00:42:49.633 --> 00:42:52.603
We'll find that out
once we examine this gun.

00:42:58.208 --> 00:43:00.644
You retrieved the gun to help Junichi?

00:44:12.950 --> 00:44:14.752
FINAL EPISODE

00:44:14.818 --> 00:44:17.988
You wanted to free Detective Tobina
from the guilt of murder.

00:44:18.055 --> 00:44:19.823
You wished to help him out
that badly, huh?

00:44:19.890 --> 00:44:21.225
Calm down, Tobina!

00:44:21.291 --> 00:44:23.560
THE SHOCKING CONCLUSION

00:44:23.627 --> 00:44:26.597
I was never able to tell you
that I like you, Makiko.

00:44:26.664 --> 00:44:27.231
GOODBYE, MY FIRST LOVE

00:44:27.297 --> 00:44:27.898
THIS DRAMA IS A FICTION

00:44:27.965 --> 00:44:28.799
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita